		     <input type="hidden" id="type"/>
			   <div class="wikiContent" id="wikiContent"  >
			        <h1 class="wikiTitle">克莱蒙特研究大学 </h1> 
					<div class="infobox"><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">	<tbody>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>排名</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>59*(1)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>国家</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>美国</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>州省</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>加利福尼亚州*(1)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>城市</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>克莱蒙特*(1)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>校训</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>Multa lumina, una lux (Latin)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>英译</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>Many flames, one light</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>性质</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>私立，男女合校*(1)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>成立年份</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>1925*(1)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>宗教信仰</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>无</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>校园</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>郊区 0.077Km<sup>2</sup>*(1)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>学生人数</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>2,160*(3)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>师生比</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>1:9*(3)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>国际学生比例</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>20%*(3)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>学校分类</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>独立机构*(1)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>所属集团</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>克莱蒙特学院</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>认证机构</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p>西部学校与学院协会（WASC）*(2)</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:35.72%">			<p>网址</p>			</td>			<td style="width:64.28%">			<p><a href="http://www.cgu.edu" target="_blank">www.cgu.edu</a></p>			</td>		</tr>	</tbody></table></div>
					<div id="content"><p>克莱蒙特研究大学（Claremont Graduate University，缩写：CGU）成立于1925年，位于美国加利福尼亚州克莱蒙特，洛杉矶市中心以东56km处，是一所私立，完全开设研究生课程研究学院，也是克莱蒙特学院的一员。</p><p>注：克莱蒙特学院是由5所本科生院和2所研究生院构成，学院间步行距离即可到达，且共享教育和学校设施资源。这种形式是仿牛津大学和剑桥大学的模式设计的。</p><p><strong>学校历史</strong></p><p>克莱蒙特研究大学成立于1925年，是克莱蒙特学院开始成立之后的第二所学院，第一所是波莫纳学院，第三所是斯克利普斯学院，也是目前美国现有仅开设研究生课程的高校中最古老的学校。克莱蒙特研究大学自成立之后，几经更名。最初沿用克莱蒙特大学学院（Claremont University College）这一名称达37年，1962年正式更名为克莱蒙特研究学校和大学中心（Claremont Graduate School and University Center），1967年，再次更名为克莱蒙特大学中心（Claremont University Center），直到1998年，才正式更为现名。</p><p>克莱蒙特大学目前有2,200名左右的硕士生和PhD学生，将近200名全职和兼职教员。卡耐基教学推进基金会（Carnegie Foundation for the Advancement of Teaching）将克莱蒙特研究大学归入非医学/兽医学领域研究活动高度活跃的综合博士点（CompDoc/NMedVet）。学校5间学院和一个独立科系提供31个学科的硕士和/或博士教学，招生名额和班级规模都很小。</p><p>克莱蒙特研究大学是美国最古老的研究机构，全球各个领域都有需要非常知名的校友。学校目前设有5个独立的学院，分别是：</p><ul>	<li>艺术与人文学院（School of Arts &amp; Humanities）</li>	<li>社区与全球卫生学院（School of Community &amp; Global Health）</li>	<li>商学院（Drucker School of Management）</li>	<li>教育研究学院（School of Educational Studies）</li>	<li>社会科学、政治与评估学院（School of Social Science, Policy, &amp; Evaluation）*(1)</li></ul><h2>学生评价</h2><p>Health &amp; Safety: Various measures are taken to make sure students have access to health and safety resources. The campus security is very prompt with responses.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Campus Housing: The student housing is nice if one doesn&#39;t have a lot of things to put in it. Since the rooms come furnished (minus the bed), it&#39;s convenient, especially for those who live far away and don&#39;t want to deal with the hassle of buying and moving furniture. The studios are tiny but if one does not have a lot of luggage and what not, it works. The refrigerators for the studios are also a joke so if one wants to cook, I would recommend either buying a bigger refrigerator, or consider moving into a unit with a regular sized refrigerator (i.e. one that has a freezer). Basically, if you opt to have roommates or can afford to/want to move into a 1-bedroom, the refrigerator issue will be resolved.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Overall Experience: A lot of people complain that the school is expensive, which is true for its PhD program. Most PhD programs fund their students but CGU doesn&#39;t seem to have that luxury. However, as a Masters student who does get some funding, I have no complaints because I know how rare it is to find a school that funds Masters students. That aside, I&#39;ve explored all the resources available to this school and I really like what CGU offers. They try to do a lot with student diversity, health, and academic help (e.g. Writing Center, digital services, library services, etc.) and I&#39;ve found the workshops they had on career development to be very helpful. I think that if one utilizes those resources, the school isn&#39;t what everyone calls &quot;overpriced.&quot; However, some of their resources are still being developed, such as the fellowship office so perhaps that&#39;s why people had/have complaints. Since it&#39;s a smaller school, the people (not only professors and advisers, but admin as well) are willing to help you out when you need it. I&#39;m finding myself to have an incredibly positive experience so far with CGU.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Overall Experience: Claremont Graduate University gives you very little compared to what they charge in tuition and many of the administrators see students as inferior. The school of community and global health at CGU is fantastic, but the university as a whole is too expensive, and not student oriented.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Majors: Great professors, interesting classes. Unclear expectations at times. The whole experience is marred by the dealings with financial aid and administration though.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Party Scene: The Village can be fun and there are places where students can go drink and have fun every week. If there is not a party at one school there is definitely something else going on at one of the colleges or you can just have your own.*(4)</p><p>参考资料：</p><p>(1)&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/School_of_the_Art_Institute_of_Chicago">School of the Art Institute of Chicago</a>&nbsp;Wikipedia</p><p>(2) <a href="http://www.cgu.edu/pages/2404.asp">Accreditation</a> Claremont Graduate University</p><p>(3) <a href="http://www.cgu.edu/pages/162.asp">CGU Facts</a> Claremont Graduate University</p><p>(4) <a href="https://colleges.niche.com/claremont-graduate-university/">Claremont Graduate University</a>&nbsp;College Prowler</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h1>研究生申请</h1><h2>基本要求</h2><ul>	<li>语言要求：TOEFL总分不低于100分，IELTS总分不低于7.5分，两者均无单项要求。如申请者语言成绩未达到上述要求，但TOEFL总分在75分以上，IELTS总分在6.0以上，可获得条件录取，入读国际学生桥梁项目（International Fellows Pathway Program）</li>	<li>学位背景要求：正规大学本科毕业并取得学士学位</li>	<li>GPA：未做要求，通常美国大学研究生院要求申请者本科GPA，尤其是大三和大四GPA不低于3.0</li></ul><ul>	<li><a href="http://www.qianmu.org/GRE" target="_blank">GRE</a>：	<ul>		<li>以下专业不要求GMAT或GRE成绩，如艺术、EMBA、高级管理硕士（MS in Advanced Management）、师范教育、商业艺术与艺术管理，其中商业艺术与艺术管理建议但不要求国际学生递交此项材料；</li>		<li>经济学和心理学专业要求递交GRE成绩，建议递交GRE相关科目成绩；</li>		<li>以下专业既接受GMAT，也接受GRE，如经济学、金融工程、人力资源管理、信息系统技术、数学、MBA、政治与政策；</li>		<li>以下专业可用MCAT取代GRE成绩，即社区与全球卫生；</li>		<li>师范教育专业要求所有申请者参加美国教师资格考试（CBEST）*(1)(2)</li>	</ul>	</li>	<li>申请时间：接受秋季、春季和夏季学期入学申请，部分专业有单独要求，请按下文申请日期*(3)</li></ul><p><strong>申请时间</strong></p><p>克莱蒙特研究大学建议申请截止日期之前递交申请，这样有助于提高入学和获奖几率。如在建议申请截止日期之前未录满，将继续接受申请，直至录满为止。</p><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">	<tbody>		<tr>			<td style="width:12.4%">			<p>申请学期</p>			</td>			<td style="width:27.44%">			<p>夏季</p>			</td>			<td style="width:5.18%">			<p>秋季</p>			</td>			<td style="width:54.98%">			<p>春季</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:12.4%">			<p>建议申请截止日期</p>			</td>			<td style="width:27.44%">			<p>3月1日</p>			</td>			<td style="width:5.18%">			<p>2月1日</p>			</td>			<td style="width:54.98%">			<p>11月1日</p>			</td>		</tr>		<tr>			<td style="width:12.4%">			<p>最终申请截止日期</p>			</td>			<td style="width:27.44%">			<p>4月1日</p>			</td>			<td style="width:5.18%">			<p>7月1日</p>			</td>			<td style="